1. Sautee garlic, broccoli, mushrooms, and any other leftover veggies in olive oil and rice vinegar. Lightly salt and pepper the mixture.

2. Add pre-cooked spaghetti squash to make it into a well-rounded, filing meal. 

3. Top with Sriracha, add salt an pepper if needed to taste.



